\begin_layout Section
DFSA with EPCglobal C1G2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section, a brief introduction about DFSA with EPCglobal C1 G2 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "standard"

\end_inset

 will be given.
 The reading process consists of multiple inventory rounds.
 Each inventory round typically has a different frame length.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Conventional-variable-frame"

\end_inset

 shows an example for the frame length adaptation in EPCglobal C1 G2.
 According to figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Conventional-variable-frame"

\end_inset

, the initial frame length is 
\begin_inset Formula $2^{Q_{ini}}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{ini}=4$
\end_inset

.
 Then each slot is checked.
 If there is no tag reply, the frame length should be decreased.
 If it is a collided slot, the frame length is increased.
 Finally, if the slot is a successful slot, the frame length will remain
 as it is.
 
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Q-slot_operation_Reader.emf
	lyxscale 20
	width 50page%

\end_inset


\end_layout

